      "source": [
        "Sure, here is a Python program that asks the user to enter student grades. If the user enters a negative value, the program stops. On the other hand, for each note entered, the program gradually builds a list. After each entry of a new note (and therefore at each iteration of the loop), it displays the number of notes entered, the highest note, the lowest note, the average of all the notes."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yOmla_98b-Go"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Create an empty list to store the grades\n",
        "grades = []\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get the user's input\n",
        "while True:\n",
        "  grade = int(input(\"Enter a grade: \"))\n",
        "\n",
        "  # If the user enters a negative value, stop the loop\n",
        "  if grade < 0:\n",
        "    break\n",
        "\n",
        "  # Add the grade to the list\n",
        "  grades.append(grade)\n",
        "\n",
        "  # Print the number of grades entered, the highest grade, the lowest grade, and the average\n",
        "  print(\"Number of grades entered:\", len(grades))\n",
        "  print(\"Highest grade:\", max(grades))\n",
        "  print(\"Lowest grade:\", min(grades))\n",
        "  print(\"Average grade:\", sum(grades) / len(grades))"
      ],
      "outputs": [],
